title: Mortgage Rates Too High? (Blame the Fed, Wall Street and Your Neighbor.)
description: Lenders use several bits of data to set mortgage rates, including trading moves by investors. Without market volatility, the rate could be under 7 percent.
dc:creator: Joe Rennison and Tara Siegel Bernard
media:credit: Philip Cheung for The New York Times
media:description: Newly built homes in California in July. High mortgage rates have put many homes out of reach for prospective buyers.
